filled_values.Dwelling Description:
The Dwelling risk is a 1 story residential building with 25 year 3 tab shingles on the roof and brick veneer on the elevations. The dwelling roof is a 5/12 one story gable roof with 25 year 3-tab shingles installed as a single layer. Felt and drip edge is present. The roof is approximately 20 years old. It has a 1 ft overhang, PVC ridge vent, and 5 pipe jacks. The front slope is North facing. The right elevation is free from wind damage. The A.C unit is free from damage.
Detached garage. The detached garage roof is comprised of 3-tab shingles, single layer, drip edge, 25 year 3-tab shingles, and has a 6/12 pitch with a PVC ridge vent. The detached garage right slope is free from wind damage. The detached garage rear slope is free from storm damage. The detached garage front elevation is free from wind damage. The detached garage right elevation is free from wind damage. The detached garage rear elevation is free from wind damage. The detached garage left elevation is free from wind damage.
filled_values.Property Condition:
The member had power outage on the DOL resulting in of food loss of $500. The dwelling roof's front slope has 13 wind damaged shingles. Missing/damaged shingles from wind. The dwelling roof's rear slope has 150 wind damaged shingles. Missing/damaged shingles from wind. The front elevation has fascia displaced. The rear elevation has fascia damaged. Fascia damaged/displaced. Missing/damaged fascia. The left elevation has fascia displaced.
Detached garage roof's left slope has 26 wind damaged shingles. Missing/damaged shingles from wind.
